    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\n\nOptimize rms_norm kernel:\n* Do vectorized load and store using `vec_n_t<scalar_t, VEC_SIZE>`.\n* Since input, weight, output tensors are the same dtype, and all of their last dimension are hidden_size, we can get the largest safe vec_size by calculating the number that can divide hidden_size and fits in 16 bytes, to avoid misalignment.\n* For large num_tokens (>=256), use smaller blocks to increase SM concurrency.\n\n## Test Plan\n\n```\npytest -s -v tests/kernels/core/test_layernorm.py\n```\n\n## Test Result\n\nUnit test passed.\n\n## Benchmark\n\nBenchmarked on p5e.48xlarge (8 H200).\n\n```\npython3 benchmarks/kernels/benchmark_rmsnorm.py\n```\n\nBaseline\n\n```\nrmsnorm-perf-without-residual:\n    head_num  batch_size  seq_len  HuggingFace   FlashInfer         vLLM\n0       32.0         1.0     64.0   172.639996     9.280000    11.712000\n1       32.0         1.0    128.0   160.976000    10.560000    13.344000\n2       32.0         1.0    256.0   160.543993    11.168000    14.176000\n3       32.0         1.0    512.0   166.176006    13.440000    18.112000\n4       32.0         1.0   1024.0   163.008004    17.759999    26.400000\n5       32.0         4.0     64.0   161.408007    11.168000    14.112000\n6       32.0         4.0    128.0   162.719995    13.152000    18.144000\n7       32.0         4.0    256.0   163.376004    17.759999    26.400000\n8       32.0         4.0    512.0   171.775997    27.200000    43.072000\n9       32.0         4.0   1024.0   270.624012    52.127998    91.168001\n10      32.0        16.0     64.0   164.095998    17.728001    26.432000\n11      32.0        16.0    128.0   170.848005    27.200000    43.104000\n12      32.0        16.0    256.0   270.559996    52.096002    91.136001\n13      32.0        16.0    512.0   492.159992    93.344003   167.392001\n14      32.0        16.0   1024.0   943.135977   176.704004   319.775999\n15      32.0        64.0     64.0   269.919991   